<h1>@HI{{sore nara}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{sore nara}}</strong> ...
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@HI{{sore nara}}</strong> is a conjunction used a the beginning of a sentence to refer to something mentioned in a previous sentence. The meaning is "in that case".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      A: @HI{{@KJ{{head}}ga @KJ{{pain}}ii desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      B: @HI{{<strong>sore nara</strong> sugu @KJ{{lie*down}}nasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      A: I have a headache.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      B: In that case, go to and lie down straightaway.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

The @HI{{sore}} in @HI{{<strong>sore nara</strong>}} refers to something in a previous sentence. The @HI{{nara}} refers to the speaker's supposition regrading the truth of the previous statement.
<p></p>

@HI{{<strong>sore nara</strong>}} has a more formal form @HI{{sore naraba}}.
<p></p>

The sentence following @HI{{<strong>sore nara</strong>}} is bound by the same restrictions that apply to @HI{{nara}}.
<p></p>

Unlike <a href="grammar-sore-dewa.html"> @HI{{sore deha}}</a>, @HI{{<strong>sore nara</strong>}} is depends on a verbal context.
<p></p>

